==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: maleic acid
<hw>maleic acid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
unsaturated dicarboxylic acid (<chform>HO.CO.CH=CH.CO.OH</chform>) of
<it>cis</it> conformation, having various uses in the manufacture of
artificial resins, the dyeing and finishing of wool, silk, and cotton,
and also combined with certain drugs to make salts more soluble than the
basic forms. The corresponding isomer having <it>trans</it>
conformation, is identical in chemical formula, is called <contr>fumaric
acid</contr>.</def> <au>MI11</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

